<div class="col two-sm last" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn2">
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Travel information</h3>
    Local directionFor directions for Chorley &amp; South Ribble District General Hospital please click on the Directions/Parking link from the Trusts Website - <br/><br/>http://www.lancsteachinghospitals.nhs.ukBus informationBus services to and from Chorley &amp; South Ribble District General Hospital are as follows; Numbers 114 119 125 126 210 301 302 C8 C9. <br/>For more information telephone: Chorley Bus Station on 01257 241693<br/>Road informationThe hospital site is three-quarters of a mile from junction 8 of the M61 motorway. <br/>Leave the motorway at Junction 8, follow signs towards Chorley (A6).<br/>At the first roundabout, turn left, continuing to head towards Chorley (A6). <br/>At the second roundabout, take second turning onto the B5252 (Euxton Lane). <br/>The main hospital entrance is 200 yards on the left at the traffic lights. <br/>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Parking</h3>
<p>Chorley &amp; South Ribble District General Hospital has three main public car-parks and two smaller parking areas, providing 256 parking spaces, of which 23 are for disabled people. Details of the new charges from July 2017<br/><br/>Up to 30 minutes	FREE<br/>Up to 1 hour	2.50<br/>Up to 2 hours	3.50<br/>Up to 4 hours	5.50<br/>Up to 6 hours	6.00<br/>Up to 8 hours	8.00<br/>More than 8 hours	10.00<br/><br/>The same charges will apply to all carpark users including Blue Badge holders. If Blue Badge holders, or anyone else using our carparks need support to park or obtain a ticket, please contact the carpark team for assistance by pressing the button at the carpark entrance barriers.</p>
